# .lizard-whitelist
#
# Functions explicitly allowlisted from the lizard complexity gate
# enforced by .github/workflows/ci.yml. Each entry is a function
# name pattern (lizard does substring matching against the fully
# qualified C++ name).
#
# This file documents acknowledged complexity debt — every entry
# has a target release for actual decomposition. The allowlist is
# a temporary tool to keep the gate green on the CURRENT state of
# the codebase while NEW violations still get caught. It is NOT a
# fix; please open a new entry only when you also pencil in the
# corresponding decomposition work into the roadmap.
#
# Format: one function name per line. Lines starting with `#` are
# comments. Blank lines ignored.

# ---- v0.22.0 decomposition targets ---------------------------------
# audio::AudioMixer::MixVoiceSound_ — CCN 34, length 196.
# The per-voice render path: combines mono/pan, binaural, and LPF
# branches in one function. v0.22.0 will split into
# MixVoiceSoundPanned_ + MixVoiceSoundBinaural_ with a shared LPF
# helper. The v0.20.2 mixer bench (~5.1µs/voice binaural, ~2.1µs/voice
# LPF, ~1.0µs/voice mono+pan) gates the decomposition against
# performance regression: ±5% at N=256 voices is the SLO.
audio::AudioMixer::MixVoiceSound_

# audio::AudioMixer::DrainCommands — CCN 30, length 174.
# Command-queue dispatcher with one branch per AudioEventType.
# v0.22.0 will decompose into per-kind handler methods. The lizard
# violation here is structural complexity, not perf (~25 ns/command
# in the v0.20.2 bench).
audio::AudioMixer::DrainCommands

# audio::ComputeLpfCoeffs — 8 params (gate is 6).
# Free function computing biquad coefficients. Eight params come
# from (cutoff, Q, sampleRate, gainDb, mix) + three coefficient
# out-params. v0.22.0 fix: bundle out-params into a Coeffs struct,
# drop param count to 5.
audio::ComputeLpfCoeffs
